Ashborn forge-culture aligns naturally with the Brawler tradition's core epistemology: knowledge that has been tested against resistance is reliable knowledge; knowledge that hasn't been tested is speculation. The pit's adversarial testing methodology is the physical analogue of forge-testing — you know what the metal can do because you've stressed it past its limits and observed where it fails. Ashborn practitioners who enter the Brawler tradition typically advance quickly through the early stages because the demonstration-based instruction model matches Ashborn learning culture, which similarly privileges hands-on direct experience over theoretical frameworks. Ashborn Brawlers in Kowloon's harbor district are disproportionately represented in the enforcement corps relative to their population, reflecting both aptitude and cultural fit with the enforcement corps' direct-action orientation.

